dataIdInfo.idPurp: The primary usefulness of the dataset is to provide users with a featureclass which can be used to spatially identify a geographic placename whether it be a city, town or village. As well, it can be use for cartographic purposes Other datasets such as address points use this dataset to identify the geographic place where they reside.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: The dataset contains the extents of the 7 area municipalites located within the Region of Waterloo, As well, it contains the extents larger towns and villages within the Region of Waterloo.

prcStep.stepDesc: Performed a 'Union" between the selected records from step one with the Municipal Boundaries featureclass
Selected records in the Settlments featureclasses where Type = Settlement Residential or Township Urban Area

Deleted any of the smaller settlement areas that would not be typically identified in an address. For example, Hwy 24 residential, Dickie One, Dickie Two, etc. Although they may be a settlement area as noted in any of the respective Local Area Municipal Official Plans they aren't typically used as an place name identifier for a municipal address.
Performed a quality control check looking for duplicate records. Might have been the result of geometry differences between the selected Settlements fc and the Municipal Boundaries fc
Corrected spelling of Philipsburg from Phillipsburg
